{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d40bce11-e2b6-4296-95b0-873c10a9e56e","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the VSTest compatibility layer is no longer included by default.**\n\nMSTest.Sdk 4.x exclusively targets Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new `dotnet test` integration) and drops the VSTest bridge adapter. This means `vstest.console.exe` can no longer discover or run your tests.\n\n### Your options:\n\n1. **Switch your CI to `dotnet test`** (recommended) — it works natively with Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET 8+.\n\n2. **Re-enable the VSTest adapter** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   or explicitly reference the bridge package:\n   ```xml\n   <ItemGroup>\n     <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" />\n   </ItemGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Stay on MSTest.Sdk 3.x** until you can migrate your pipeline away from `vstest.console`.\n\nThe recommended path forward is option 1 — replace `vstest.console` invocations in your CI with `dotnet test`, which natively supports the new testing platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f7ac19e-2ad8-42c3-b73f-cc7e98f16d82","outputTokens":317,"requestId":"8439:A775:23FF574:278BD2A:6A0AD7F1"},"id":"c4f8aaee-c1f9-410d-b1a6-70039c8b3672","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:12:25.859Z","parentId":"0d16a59e-343b-428b-8570-2958c119d1ab"}
